\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Determine their requirements and expectations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Manage their influence in relation to the requirements.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Stakeholders who ignore their responsibility can have a damaging impact
 on the project.
 Likewise, project managers who ignore stakeholders can also expect a damaging
 impact on project outcomes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Any project can have positive and negative stakeholders.
 For example, in new construction, the local businesses would be the positive
 stakeholders and environmental groups would be the negative stakeholders
 (project completion would be a negative for them).
\end_layout

