\begin_layout Enumerate
Contract Types
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The type of contract used and the terms and conditions set the degree of
 risk being assumed by the buyer and seller.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Contracts fall into 3 categories:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Fixed-price or lump-sum contracts.
 Involves a fixed total price for a well-defined product.
 The simplest form is a purchase order for a specified item to be delivered
 by a specified date for a specified price.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Cost-reimbursable contracts.
 Involves payment to the seller for the seller’s actual cost, plus a fee
 typically representing profit.
 Costs are classified as Direct Costs, costs incurred for the exclusive
 benefit of the project (e.g., salaries), Indirect Costs, overhead and administrat
ive costs, usually calculated as percentage of direct costs.
 Three common types of cost-reimbursable contacts:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Cost-Plus-Fee (CPF) or Cost-Plus-Percentage of Cost (CPPC).
 Seller is reimbursed for the costs performing the contract and receives
 a fee calculated as an agreed-upon percentage of the costs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Cost-Plus-Fixed Fee (CPFF).
 Seller is reimbursed for the costs performing the contract plus a fixed
 fee payment calculated as a percentage of the estimated projects costs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Cost-Plus-Incentive-Fee (CPIF).
 Seller is reimbursed for the costs performing the contract plus a predetermined
 fee based upon achieving certain performance objectives.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Time and Material (T&M) contracts.
 A hybrid of the other two types.
 The full value of the agreement is not determined at the time of the award.
 T&M contracts can grow in value as if they were cost-reimbursable arrangements.
 Also, they can resemble fixed-priced contracts because unit rates can be
 preset by the buyer and seller.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
